\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Ana-Diaz-Green-Purple.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=48 1x, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Ana-Diaz-Green-Purple.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96 2x\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Ana-Diaz-Green-Purple.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/authors/ana-diaz\"\u003eAna Diaz\u003c/a\u003e \u003cspan\u003e(she/her) is a culture writer at Polygon, covering internet culture, fandom, and video games. Her work has previously appeared at NPR, Wired, and The Verge.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"zephr-anchor\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLockpicks \u003c/strong\u003eare an item that allow you to open locked doors and chests to get loot in \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/the-elder-scrolls-4-oblivion/4597\"\u003eThe Elder Scrolls 4: Oblivion Remastered\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eA lockpick gives you a chance to open a lock on a chest or door via successful completion of an instance of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/elder-scrolls-4-oblivion-remastered-guides/562559/lockpicking-how-to-lockpick\"\u003elockpicking\u003c/a\u003e minigame. The lockpicking system can be tricky; if you make mistakes, it’s easy to burn through several lockpicks on a single lock. As such, you might need a ton of lockpicks.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere’s \u003cstrong\u003ewhere to buy lockpicks\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cem\u003eOblivion Remastered\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"where-to-buy-lockpicks-in-oblivion-remastered\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eWhere to buy lockpicks in Oblivion Remastered\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlthough lockpicks aren’t sold by your usual town merchants, there are several locations where you can buy lockpicks. Below, we highlight some of the easiest places to buy lockpicks in \u003cem\u003eOblivion Remastered\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A graphic showing two side by side images. The image on the left shows a map with a marker pinned to the northwestern corner of Imperial City. The left image shows Shady Sam standing outside the castle wall. \" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-8.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%