ockpicks is to hit up \u003cstrong\u003eShady Sam\u003c/strong\u003e, the merchant. \u003cstrong\u003eOne lockpick costs 6 gold\u003c/strong\u003e and you can buy up to 30 lockpicks each day. You can find Shady Sam northwest of the Imperial City. He is located outside the city walls, just outside where the Elven Gardens district is.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne limited way you can buy lockpicks is by \u003cstrong\u003estarting the quest to join the Thieves Guild\u003c/strong\u003e and talking to \u003cstrong\u003eArmand Christophe \u003c/strong\u003eat the Imperial City Waterfront. He’ll sell you \u003cstrong\u003elockpicks for 5 gold\u003c/strong\u003e each. It’s a good deal, but you need to activate the quest to talk to him and he leaves once you progress the quest. See our guide on how to join the \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/elder-scrolls-4-oblivion-remastered-guides/565586/thieves-guild-how-to-join\"\u003eThieves Guild\u003c/a\u003e for more details.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eOnce you join the Thieves Guild, \u003cstrong\u003eyou can buy lockpicks from fences\u003c/strong\u003e, the term for characters who buy stolen property.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-9.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A graphic showing two side by side images. The image on the left shows a map with a marker on the southern tip of Bruma. The left image shows Ongar in his house. \" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/04/Untitled-design-9.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygo